Full Title: Conference on Modern Cross-Cultural Research 
Short Title: MCR 2006 

Date: 21-Oct-2006 - 21-Oct-2006
Location: Kaohsiung, Taiwan 
Contact Person: Hsin Xin Huang
Meeting Email: ineststs@yahoo.com.tw

Linguistic Field(s): Ling & Literature 

Subject Language(s): English (eng)

Call Deadline: 11-Aug-2006 

Meeting Description:

Conference Objectives:
MCR 2006 is devoted to the study of cross-cultural understanding with a 
clear humanistic emphasis. It aims to promote the exchange of research 
findings among graduate students in the related fields of Philosophy, 
Arts, Linguistics, and Literature. 

MCR 2006 Conference on Modern Cross-Cultural Research
Call for Papers

Organizer?College of Liberal Arts, National Sun-Yat Sen University
Conference Date: Saturday, October 21st, 2006
Conference Location: National Sun-Yat Sen University, Taiwan

Important Dates:
1.  Abstract Submission Deadline: August 11th, 2006
2.  Acceptance notification: August, 30th, 2006
3.  Date of Conference: Saturday, October 21st, 2006

Conference Objectives:
MCR 2006 is devoted to the study of cross-cultural understanding with a 
clear humanistic emphasis. It aims to promote the exchange of research 
findings among graduate students in the related fields of Philosophy, 
Arts, 
Linguistics, and Literature.

Conference Themes:
The conference theme for this year is modern cross-culture research, 
which 
includes:
-         Aesthetics and/or Art History
-          Chinese Literature Studies
-          Culture Policy
-          Literature and Theory
-          Performance
-          Race, Class, Gender in Literature
-          Social Criticism and Culture Studies
-          Cross-Cultural Communication

Submission Procedure:
Submissions of abstracts will be invited for 20-minute presentation 
(followed by a 10-minute discussion).  We welcome studies on the 
conference 
theme or any topic related to or integrating the following areas, 
Philosophy, Linguistics, Arts, and Literature.  Please send your 
500-word 
abstract as an MS Word or PDF attachment to our e-mail address:  In the 
body 
of your e-mail message, please indicate the following information:
1.  Title
2.  Author(s): Name(s), affiliation, phone number, and email addresses
3.  Topic Area: Area and sub-area (e.g., Linguistics: Syntax)
4.  Keywords: Up to 5 keywords
5.  Audiovisual/computer equipment requirements

Languages:
English or Chinese

Contact Information:
Address:  College of Liberal Arts, National Sun Yat-sen University, 70 
Lien-Hai Rd., Kaohsiung 804, Taiwan
Phone: 886-7-5252000 ext. 3001
Email address: chuca@mail.nsysu.edu.tw; nsysumcr2006@hotmail.com




